def: A lady superior of a priory of nuns, and next in dignity to anabbess.
Sipping often. [Obs.] "Taken after a sippling sort." Holland.
An alkaloid which is the active principle of tobacco. It is acolorless, transparent, oily liquid, having an acrid odor, and anacrid burning taste. It is intensely poisonous. Ure.

Applied to the peculiar wormlike wave motion of the intestinesand other similar structures, produced by the successive contractionof the muscular fibers of their walls, forcing their contentsonwards; as, peristaltic movement.-- Per`i*stal"tic*al*ly, adv.
Old beer; sharp or strong liquor. [Old Slang]Shall I set a cup of old stingo at your elbow Addison.
A game played with nine pins, or pieces of wood, set on end, atwhich a wooden ball is bowled to knock them down; bowling.
Belonging to Lent; used in Lent; Lenten.
